Something in here should probably be async, shouldn't it? i.e. the completion might take some time to find? I'm tempted with the history api to make this method return an NSOperation so that we have some way to cancel in progress tasks. But I'd also like to just tie this to the list history api. I wonder if we can do something like:

```
locationTextField.textChangeDelegate = tabsViewController
tabsViewController {
    func textField(textField: UITextField, shouldChangeCharactersInRange range: NSRange, replacementString string: String) -> Bool {
       // When the text changes, fire off an async history request
       history.filter(searchString) { sites in
             viewController.data = sites
             locationTextField.autocompletion = findCompletion(sites, searchString)
       }
}
```

